# 8. 街の灯

An: ...is what happened.
Rin & Kohane: Wow!
Rin: Nagi was so cool! She went to rescue you from that construction site like a superhero!
Kohane: Yeah...! She sounded so amazing! And really reliable!
Toya: Yes, she did. Your story gave us a very clear picture of what she's like.
Akito: Yeah, she seems like a really good person. I guess you've gotta be to sing alongside Ken and Taiga.
KAITO: Still, your past self probably wouldn't believe that you ended up enrolling in the school you snuck into that time...
Luka: Also, An, I vaguely remember hearing something about you being afraid of ghosts... Is that because...?
An: Um, well... That's not important!
Luka: Hehe. Yes, I suppose so. You can tell us all about it later!
An: No, we don't have to talk about it at all!
Miku: In any case, it was nice to finally hear more about Nagi.
Miku: I understand now that she's very similar to you, An.
An: What?! Similar to me?!
An: A-Are you sure...? She always seemed so much cooler and...
Miku: At the very least, she had a big influence on you growing up, right? That's what I took away from your story.
An: Yeah, I guess she did...
An: Even now, I feel like I'm chasing after trying to become a cool lady like her...
An: Especially since she was the one who made me realize just how much I love everyone around town.
An: And how I want to learn to love this city even more...
Akito: Learn to love...
Akito: This city... Even more, huh?
Toya: Oh...
Kohane: Is something wrong, you two?
Akito: Not wrong, but... That reminded me of something Tono said when we talked the other day.
An: What did it remind you of...?
Toya: What Taiga said to Tono after he lost to him in a battle.
Toya: He said, “Take a look at this city.”
Len: Take a look at the city...? What's that supposed to mean?
Akito: Tono doesn't seem to know and neither do we... It's a total mystery...
An: Uncle Taiga said that to Arata?! The city...? This city...?
Kohane: Wait, Taiga told me the same thing when I was practicing with him...!
Akito: He did?
Kohane: Yeah. We even took walks around Vivid Street together.
Toya: I see... So Taiga believes that we need to at least “take a look at this city” if we actually wish to surpass RAD WEEKEND.
Akito: But what exactly are we supposed to be looking for...? I doubt he meant just literally looking at stuff around town.
MEIKO: Right. Based on what you've all said, physically looking seems to be a small part of a bigger picture.
Rin: Hmm... Well, you can find live houses and record stores... Is there anything else that comes to mind?
An: Other than those things...? People, I guess...?
An: This may just be me, but everyone in Vivid Street's really friendly and loves music...
An: But if they weren't like that, we'd probably be talking about a pretty different place.
Akito: Yeah... I have to agree based on your story, An.
Len: Hang on. What does knowing what everyone's like have to do with music?
Kohane: I'm not really sure, but Taiga talks about those kinds of “practices” a lot so they must be related somehow...
Rin: Oh, what if you're supposed to put on an event and invite all the locals to be in the audience?
Luka: Didn't they do precisely that during their last event?
Toya: Yes, we did. Some weren't from Vivid Street, but most were local residents or musicians who've been performing there for a long time.
Rin: Hmm... Then, that's not the answer...
An: Still, “taking a look at this city” does seem really important...
An: Aunt Nagi also cared a lot about everyone around town...
Toya: Very true... Let's keep doing our best to unravel this enigma...
An & Kohane: Yeah!
An: Oh, it's getting pretty late...! We've been brainstorming for a while now.
Toya: Yes, we have. We should head home soon before we all get scolded.
Akito: At least we won't have the police coming after us like An.
An: Was that really necessary?
Kohane: Hehe. Oh...
Live House Manager: Hey, An! How's it going?
Veteran Staff: Hi, everyone. Welcome back. I heard that the last VBS event was a huge hit. Way to go!
An: Hehe. You should both come see us next time! Oh, or should we just have here be our next venue?♪
Live House Manager: That'd be great! Our place can be the site of your very own legend!
Kohane: Hehe...
Kohane: (Everybody loves An so much.)
Kohane: Uh oh...! Sorry, I really need to get home soon or else my dad's going to start worrying!
Toya: Same. Why don't we call things here?
Akito: Yeah. See you guys later.
An: Okay, everyone! Bye bye! We'll see you guys later too!
Live House Manager: Yeah, see you tomorrow!
An: I'm back!
An's Father: Hey, welcome back. You were out pretty late today.
An: Yup! On top of practicing, we spent a lot of time discussing our next event and talking about all sorts of other stuff.
An: Oh, I even got to tell Kohane and the others about Aunt Nagi today.
An's Father: About Nagi?
An: Yeah. They all seem to believe that she was central to making RAD WEEKEND what it was.
An: Haha. I mean, I know all three of you were key figures, but the way Aunt Nagi kicked things off left a huge impression on everyone.
An: Her first song left me totally stunned too!
An's Father: I see...
An: A few questions later, I was telling them a story about Aunt Nagi.
An: Remember when I was still in elementary school and ran away? I told them about how she found me that time!
An's Father: Yeah... I remember.
An: Hehe. The worried look I saw on your face that time made me so happy too.
An: It felt really rare because you always seem so calm and collected, Dad!
An's Father: Hold on. I worry about things just like anyone else.
An: Are you sure about that? I haven't seen you like that ever since...
An: Oh, speaking of which...
An: After telling everyone about Aunt Nagi, I was told that I'm a lot like her... What do you think? Am I?
An: I really hope that I have made some progress since I've sorta been chasing after her...!
An's Father: You and Nagi...?
An's Father: Yeah, you two are alike...
An: We are? Hehe. Hearing that from you makes me so happy!
An: Alright, I'm gonna keep doing my best to be like Aunt Nagi in order to surpass RAD WEEKEND!
An's Father: I'm not sure how I feel about you becoming that relentless...
An's Father: Anyway, An, we shouldn't be getting any more customers, so can you start locking up for me?
An: Oh, sure! I'll switch the sign to closed!
An: Okay, the plate's flipped...
An: Oh wow... The sky's so clear tonight! And the stars look so pretty!
An: (But...)
An: (The city lights seem even prettier for some reason. Why is that?)
An: (Through the eyes of someone not from here, this place can seem pretty rough or dangerous.)
Nagi: They all care about you just this much.
An: (Maybe it's because I know everyone from around town's here...and doing their best...)
An: *Sigh* What are you up to right now in America, Aunt Nagi? I really wish you'd send a message or something every once in a while.
An: Oh, I can send her one! That might take her by surprise!
An: I wanna tell her all about the others, the events we've been doing and lots more...!
An: Alright, I'm gonna do everything I can for our next event! I'm gonna make it so I stun her the next time she sees me!
An's Father: ...
An: They all seem to believe that Nagi was central to making RAD WEEKEND what it was.
An's Father: ...
An's Father: (The time to tell them appears to be fast approaching...)
